label: draft sequence repository contextual data standard
definition: This draft specification provides a collection of fields related to the contextual data of a specimen, its genomic sequencing, and its pathogenic epidemiology.
ui_label: draft sequence repository contextual data standard

label: contact specification - specimen related organization
definition: Contact information for an organization related to specimen collection, processing or storage.

label: organization name
definition: A textual identifier for an organization. [def-source: NCI]

label: First Name
definition: A word or group of words indicating a person's first (personal or given) name; the name that precedes the surname.

label: Last Name
definition: A word or group of words indicating a person's last (family) name.

label: Job Title
definition: A local name for an individual's occupation.
help: Where personnel turnover may affect the ability for follow up, the contact information can be supplied for a job position rather than a specific individual.

label: E-mail Address
definition: A text string identifier for a location to which e-mail can be delivered.

label: Telephone Number
definition: A sequence of decimal digits (0-9) that is used for identifying a destination telephone line or other device in a telephone network.

label: Country
definition: A collective generic term that refers here to a wide variety of dependencies, areas of special sovereignty, uninhabited islands, and other entities in addition to the traditional countries or independent states.

label: United States of America
definition: A federal constitutional republic comprising fifty states and a federal district.

label: Caribbean Sea
definition: A sea situated between the northern coast of South America, the eastern coast of Central America and the islands of the West Indies.

label: English Channel
definition: A channel situated between the southern coast of England and the northern coast of France and linking the North Sea and the Celtic Sea, are the following: On the North: The southern coast of England, from Land's End (50 Degrees 04 Minutes 06 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 42 Minutes 54 Seconds W) eastward to Hope Point (51 Degrees 10 Minutes N - 1 Degrees 24 Minutes 14 Seconds E).

label: Irish Sea
definition: A sea situated between the eastern coast of Ireland and the western coasts of Scotland, England and Wales, are the following: On the North: A line joining Ballyquintin Point (54 Degrees 19 Minutes 55 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 30 Minutes W), in Ireland, northeastward to the southeastern extremity of Mull of Galloway (54 Degrees 38 Minutes N - 4 Degrees 51 Minutes 20 Seconds W), in Scotland (the common limit with the Inner Seas).

label: Mediterranean Sea
definition: An enclosed sea opening only, on the West, to the North Atlantic Ocean through the Strait of Gibraltar and, on the Northeast, to the Sea of Marmara through the Dardanelles (Canakkale Strait).

label: first-order administrative region
definition: A primary administrative division of a country, such as a state in the United States.

label: Province
definition: A region, district or division of a country; a tract; a portion a state, especially one remote from the capital.

label: Province of Alberta
definition: One of Canada's prairie provinces.

label: Province of British Columbia
definition: The westernmost of Canada's provinces.

label: Province of Manitoba
definition: One of Canada's 10 provinces.

label: Province of New Brunswick
definition: One of Canada's three Maritime provinces.

label: Province of Newfoundland and Labrador
definition: A province of Canada, the tenth and latest to join the Confederation.

label: Province of Nova Scotia
definition: A Canadian province located on Canada's southeastern coast.

label: Province of Ontario
definition: A province located in the central part of Canada.

label: Province of Prince Edward Island
definition: A Canadian province consisting of an island of the same name.

label: Province of Quebec
definition: A province in the central part of Canada.

label: Province of Saskatchewan
definition: A prairie province in Canada.

label: Puntarenas Province
definition: A province of Costa Rica.

label: Bali Province
definition: A province of Indonesia with the provincial capital at Denpasar towards the south of the island.

label: Papua Province
definition: The largest province of Indonesia, comprising a majority part of the western half of the island of New Guinea and nearby islands (see also Western New Guinea).

label: State
definition: A constituent administrative district of a nation.

label: Territory
definition: A geographical area under the jurisdiction of a sovereign state and marked off for administrative or other purposes.

label: Australian Antarctic Territory
definition: The part of Antarctica claimed by Australia.

label: Australian Capital Territory
definition: The capital territory of the Commonwealth of Australia and its smallest self-governing internal territory.

label: Coral Sea Islands Territory
definition: A Territory of Australia which includes a group of small and mostly uninhabited tropical islands and reefs in the Coral Sea, northeast of Queensland, Australia.

label: Heard Island and McDonald Islands Territory
definition: A group of uninhabited, barren islands located in the Southern Ocean, about two-thirds of the way from Madagascar to Antarctica, or 7718 km due south of Rajapur, Maharashtra.

label: Jervis Bay Territory
definition: A territory of the Commonwealth of Australia.

label: Northern Territory
definition: A federal territory of Australia, occupying much of the center of the mainland continent, as well as the central northern regions.

label: Territory of Ashmore and Cartier Islands
definition: A Territory of Australia that includes two groups of small low-lying uninhabited tropical islands in the Indian Ocean situated on the edge of the continental shelf north-west of Australia and south of the Indonesian island of Roti.

label: Territory of Christmas Island
definition: A small territory of Australia located in the Indian Ocean, 2600 km northwest of Perth in Western Australia, 500 km south of Jakarta, Indonesia, and 975 km ENE of the Cocos (Keeling) Islands.

label: Territory of Norfolk Island
definition: A Territory of Australia that includes Norfolk Island and neighboring islands.

label: Territory of the Cocos (Keeling) Islands
definition: A territory of Australia.

label: Northwest Territories
definition: A territory of Canada.

label: Nunavut
definition: The largest and newest territory of Canada; it was separated officially from the Northwest Territories on 1999-04-01.

label: Yukon
definition: The westernmost of Canada's three territories.

label: Australian Antarctic Territory
definition: The part of Antarctica claimed by Australia.

label: Unincorporated Territory (USA)
definition: An area of the United States of America under United States jurisdiction, to which Congress has determined that only select parts of the United States of America Constitution apply.

label: American Samoa
definition: An unincorporated territory of the United States located in the South Pacific Ocean, southeast of the sovereign State of Samoa.

label: Commonwealth of Puerto Rico
definition: A semi-autonomous territory composed of an archipelago in the northeastern Caribbean, east of the Dominican Republic and west of the Virgin Islands, approximately 2,000 km off the coast of Florida (the nearest of the mainland United States).

label: Territory of Guam
definition: An unincorporated territory of the United States.

label: United States Minor Outlying Islands
definition: A statistical designation defined by ISO3166-1, consists of nine insular United States possessions.

label: United States Virgin Islands
definition: A group of islands in the Caribbean that are an insular area of the United States.

label: subnational region
definition: A subnational region is a type of subnational entity similar to a nation's state, province, or territory.

label: Autonomous Region (China)
definition: A first-level administrative subdivision of China.

label: Azores
definition: A Portuguese archipelago in the Atlantic Ocean.

label: Region (contiguous United States of America)
definition: Census Regions and Divisions are groupings of States that subdivide the United States.

label: Midwest Region
definition: A census region in the United States of America

label: Northeast Region
definition: A census region in the United States of America

label: South Region
definition: A census region in the United States of America

label: West Region
definition: A census region in the United States of America

label: Hong Kong
definition: A special administrative region of the People's Republic of China (PRC).

label: Macau
definition: One of the two special administrative regions of the People's Republic of China, the other being Hong Kong.

label: East Midlands Region
definition: One of the regions of England and consists of most of the eastern half of the traditional region of the Midlands.

label: East Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England.

label: Greater London Region
definition: The top-level administrative subdivision covering London, England.

label: North East Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England and comprises the combined area of Northumberland, County Durham, Tyne and Wear, part of North Yorkshire and Tees Valley.

label: North West Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England.

label: South East Region
definition: One of the nine official regions of England.

label: South West Region
definition: One of the regions of England.

label: West Midlands Region
definition: An official region of England, covering the western half of the area traditionally known as the Midlands.

label: Yorkshire and the Humber
definition: One of the nine government office regions of England.

label: Municipality
definition: A political unit, such as a city, town, or village, incorporated for local self-government.

label: populated place, Canada
definition: A populated place.

populated place, Republic of South Africa
populated place, Zambia
definition: A small town and administrative district in the Western Province of Zambia, on the plains west of the Zambezi River and the Barotse Floodplain, about 70 km from the border with Angola.

label: populated place, contiguous United States of America
township
definition: A township is a rural or sub-urban settlement.

label: Street Address
definition: The street name and building number where a person or organization can be found.
help: The Street Address should include the building number and street name.

label: draft sequence repository data - specimen collection
draft sequence repository data - geographic location
definition: The geographical origin of the sample by city, region, country or latitude and logitude.

label: INSDC country qualifier
definition: The INSDC country qualifier is a textual controlled vocabulary used to indicate the country of origin of a DNA sample.  It can also have the following format: country:sub_region, such as: "Canada:Vancouver".

label: latitude and longitude coordinate (ISO 6709)
help: Use ISO 6709 standard. Values should be stored in signed decimal degrees format based on the WGS84 geodetic reference system. Multiple value pairs may be entered if the site is not a point. Latitude and longitude should not be abstracted to the centre of a city, province/state or country as this may falsely implicate an existing location.

label: latitude (ISO 6709)
definition: A decimal latitude measurement in degrees in conformance with the ISO 6709 standard.

label: longitude (ISO 6709)
definition: A decimal longitude measurement in degrees in conformance with the ISO 6709 standard.

label: specimen extraction location - state/province/territory/region
definition: A specimen extraction location - city or region is the Gazetteer ontology identifier or textual name of the most precise geographical location available for the site of a specimen extraction event.

label: specimen extraction location - city
definition: The specimen extraction location - city is the city where a specimen was taken (extracted) from a subject or environment

label: specimen extraction location - geographic feature
definition: A geographic location where a given specimen was extracted or collected from. Location can be identified at country, city, postal address, or longitude and latitude level of granularity. It can also be described by biome, physiographic and other environmental features.

label: anthropogenic geographic feature
definition: An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.

label: farm
definition: A tract of crop or grazing land, as well as the group of buildings with and often surrounding a farmhouse, including barns, sheds, and other outbuildings, used for agricultural production.

label: fish farm
definition: A facility in which fish are raised commercially in tanks or enclosures, usually for food.

label: fish hatchery
definition: A facility where eggs of fish are hatched under artificial conditions.

label: plantation
definition: An intentional planting of a crop, on a large scale, usually for uses other than cereal production or pasture.

label: feedlot
definition: A feedlot is a plot of land on which livestock are fattened for market

label: drylot
definition: A drylot is an enclosure of limited size usually bare of vegetation and used for fattening livestock.

label: construction
definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

label: building
definition: A permanent walled and roofed construction.

label: hospital
definition: A hospital is a building in which health care services are  provided by specialized staff and equipment.

label: house
definition: A house is a building that provides a dwelling-place for a living entity.

label: animal house
definition: A house used for sheltering non-human animals.

label: closed animal house
definition: An animal house which has a complete building envelope.

label: open animal house
definition: An animal house which is only partially surrounded by a building envelope.

label: residential building
definition: A human house which serves as a long-term shelter for its inhabitants and within which they store personal property.

label: industrial building
definition: An industrial building is a building within which goods are produced and, optionally, stored or within which services are rendered.

label: bakery
definition: A bakery is a building in which raw flour-based food is baked in an oven to produce food products such as bread, cakes, pastries, and pies.

label: brewery
definition: A brewery is a building in which alcoholic beverages are produced by brewing, that is, steeping a starch source (commonly cereal grains) in water and fermenting the resulting sweet liquid with yeast.

label: dairy
definition: A dairy is a building in which animal milk is harvested and, optionally, processed for human consumption.

label: food processing building
definition: A food processing building is a building in which materials that contain or consist of essential body nutrients - such as carbohydrates, fats, proteins, vitamins, or minerals - and may be ingested and assimilated by an organism to produce energy, stimulate growth, and maintain life are converted alternative forms.

label: fish processing building
definition: A building in which fish are subject to a series of operations to prepare them for human consumption.

label: abattoir
definition: A facility in which non-human animals are slaughtered and processed for human consumption.

label: shop
definition: A building in which a business presents a selection of goods and offers to trade or sell them to customers for money or other goods.

label: food shop
definition: A shop in which a business offers food products for sale or trade.

label: ethnic food shop
definition: A food shop in which the food products on offer are restricted to those produced in a region and cultural setting other than that of the shop's locality.

label: grocery store
definition: A food shop in which food products are the primary offer for sale or trade.

label: delicatessen
definition: A food shop which sells a selection of food products that are not typical dietary components of the human population it is co-located with.

label: grocery store
definition: A grocery store is a retail store that primarily sells food.

label: market
definition: A market, or marketplace, is a location where people regularly gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods

label: specialty/ethnic store
definition: A specialty/ethnic food store is a store specializing in a particular variety of food or food of cultural / regional origin.

label: day care building
definition: A building which is used to care for a human child during the working day by a person, outside the child's immediate family, other than that child's legal guardians.

label: food kiosk
definition: A kiosk from which food products are sold.

label: kiosk
definition: A booth with an open window on one side.

label: nursing home
definition: A building in which nursing aides and skilled nurses provide care and treatment to residents who have significant difficulty coping with the required activities of daily living.

label: restaurant
definition: A building within which food and drink are prepared and served to customers in exchange for money or other goods and/or services.

label: cafeteria
definition: A building which provides the site for food services with little or no waiting staff furnishing table service.

label: take-out restaurant
definition: A restaurant which provides prepared meals or other food products that the purchaser must eat off its premises.

label: building floor
definition: A building floor is a surface layer which is part of a building and used for walking.

label: constructed barrier
definition: A constructed barrier is a freestanding wall, berm, or fence built to limit movement of entities across a boundary.

label: dam
definition: A barrier constructed across a watercourse to control the flow or raise the level of water.

label: drainage canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used drainage.

label: mine
definition: An excavation in the Earth for the purpose of extracting earth materials.

label: pier
definition: A raised walkway over water, supported by piles or pillars.

label: research facility
definition: A facility, permanent or temporary, on land, in air, space or water, where scientific research or measurements can be undertaken.

label: sports facility
definition: A building or region where sports activities can be carried out.

label: constructed swimming pool
definition: A construction which is designed to hold water in which humans may swim or perform other leisure activities.

label: water intake
definition: A hydraulic-engineering installation which transports water - in specified amounts, of a specified quality, and in accordance with a water-consumption plan - from a source of supply into a conduit.

label: garden
definition: An enclosure for displaying selected plant or animal life.

label: zoological garden
definition: A facility in which animals are confined within enclosures and displayed to the public, and in which they may also be bred.

label: petting zoo
definition: A petting zoo is a zoological garden which contains domesticated non-human animals and some wild non-human animals that are docile enough for humans to touch and feed.

label: park
definition: A bounded area of land, or water, usually in its natural or semi-natural (landscaped) state and set aside for some purpose, usually to do with recreation or conservation.

label: well
definition: A cylindrical hole, pit, or tunnel drilled or dug down to a depth from which water, oil, or gas can be pumped or brought to the surface.

label: campground
definition: A part of an ecosystem which may be or has been used for one or more overnight stays by humans sheltering in tents, camper vans, caravans, or improvised shelters.

label: dedicated campground
definition: A campground which has been modified by humans to provide and maintain facilities for camping such as fire pits, road access, latrines, and garbage bins.

label: impromptu campground
definition: A campground which has no pre-existing facilities installed or maintained by humans, usually found outside of anthropised ecosystems.

label: fairground
definition: A part of an ecosystem which has been allocated to host a gathering of people for multiple entertainment or commercial activities.

label: agricultural fairground
definition: A fairground which is used to exhibit agricultural technology, livestock, and farm-related activity.

label: market
definition: A part of an ecosystem where people gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods.

label: biome
definition: A biome is an environmental system to which resident ecological communities have evolved adaptations.

label: freshwater biome
definition: A biome that applies to the freshwater realm.

label: marine biome
definition: An aquatic biome that comprises systems of open-ocean and unprotected coastal habitats, characterized by exposure to wave action, tidal fluctuation, and ocean currents as well as systems that largely resemble these.

label: ocean biome
definition: The ocean biome comprises major bodies of saline water, principal components of the hydrosphere.

label: terrestrial biome
definition: A biome that applies to the terrestrial realm.

label: anthropogenic terrestrial biome
definition: An anthropogenic terrestrial biome is a terrestrial biome which has community structures determined by human activity.

label: cropland biome
definition: A cropland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for agricultural activity and which contains no village or larger human settlement.

label: dense settlement biome
definition: A dense settlement biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for human habitation, recreation, and industry within built structures with little other land use.

label: rangeland biome
definition: A rangeland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for the rearing and grazing of livestock.

label: village biome
definition: A village biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which contains settlements such as villages, towns, and/or small cities and which is primarily used for agricultural activity.

label: desert biome
definition: A desert biome is a terrestrial biome which loses more liquid water by evapotranspiration than is supplied by precipitation and includes communities adapted to these conditions.

label: forest biome
definition: A forest biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, densely packed vegetation which strongly limits light penetration to the forest floor.

label: grassland biome
definition: A grassland biome is a terrestrial biome which  includes, across its entire spatial extent, an unbroken layer of grasses (Gramineae), sedges (Cyperaceae) or  rushes (Juncaceae).

label: mangrove biome
definition: A mangrove biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, mangrove plants (Rhizophoraceae).

label: shrubland biome
definition: A shrubland biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, dense groups of shrubs.

label: tundra biome
definition: A tundra is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, only low-growing vegetation such as dwarf shrubs, sedges and grasses, mosses, and lichens.

label: woodland biome
definition: A woodland biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, woody plants spaced sufficiently far apart to allow light penetration to support communities of herbaceous plants or shrubs living closer to the woodland floor.

label: badland
definition: An arid terrain with clay-rich soil that has been extensively eroded by wind and water.

label: beach
definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a body of water.

label: cave
definition: Naturally formed, subterranean open area or chamber.

label: depression
definition: A landform sunken or depressed below the surrounding area.

label: channel of a watercourse
definition: The physical confine of a river, slough or ocean strait consisting of a bed and banks.

label: canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used for navigation, drainage or irrigation.

label: drainage canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used drainage.

label: ditch
definition: A small, human-made channel which has been dug for draining or irrigating the land.

label: drainage ditch
definition: A ditch that collects water from the surrounding land.

label: irrigation ditch
definition: A ditch that supplies water to surrounding land.

label: plumbing drain
definition: An artificial channel which transports unwanted water or waste liquids away from their source, either to a more useful area, a receptacle, or into sewers or stormwater mains as waste discharge to be released or processed.

label: desert
definition: A region rendered barren or partially barren by environmental extremes, especially by low rainfall.

label: plain
definition: A region of general uniform slope, comparatively level, and of considerable extent.

label: slope
definition: The part of an elevation or depression between the relatively flat surrounding area and the peak of a mount or the bottom of a depression.

label: terrace
definition: A step-like feature between higher and lower ground: a relatively flat or gently inclined shelf of earth, backed and fronted by steep slopes or manmade detaining walls.

label: tunnel
definition: An underground or underwater passage.

label: watershed
definition: The separation between neighbouring drainage basins (catchments).

label: channel
definition: A structure which traverses a mass of one or more environmental materials, and encloses a roughly tubular site.

label: tunnel
definition: An underground or underwater passage.

label: specimen type (host or environmental context)
definition: The type of material from which the specimen was obtained. Specimens are usually categorized as food, body products or tissues, or environmental material.

label: specimen collection time measurement datum
definition: A time measurement datum that is the measure of the time when the specimens are collected.
help: The sample collection date should be recorded as YYYY-MM-DD according to ISO 8601.

label: specimen collection process
definition: A planned process with the objective of collecting a specimen.
help: Collection Methods are not always known, however when specified, they should be selected from an ontology controlled vocabulary.

label: collecting specimen from organism
definition: a process with the objective to obtain a material entity that was part of an organism for potential future use in an investigation

label: Amniocentesis
definition: A prenatal diagnostic procedure in which a small sample of amniotic fluid is removed from the uterus by a needle inserted into the abdomen.

label: Aspiration
definition: Procedure using suction, usually with a thin needle and syringe, to remove bodily fluid or tissue.

label: Biopsy
definition: The removal of tissue specimens or fluid from the living body for microscopic examination, performed to establish a diagnosis.

label: Phlebotomy
definition: The collection of blood from a vein, most commonly via needle venipuncture.

label: exudate collection
definition: The process of collecting bodily fluids that have been discharged from blood vessels usually arising from inflammation or injury.

label: feces collection
definition: The process of collecting a portion of feces from an organism.

label: lavage
definition: A protocol application to separate cells and/or cellular secretions from an anatomical space by the introduction and removal of fluid

label: bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL)
definition: A technique by which cells and fluid from bronchioles and lung alveoli are removed for diagnosis of disease or evaluation of treatment.

label: rinsing for specimen collection
definition: The process of removal and collection of specimen material from the surface of an entity by washing, or a similar application of fluids.

label: plant rinse
definition: The process of rinsing plants with liquid with the objective of extracting specimens from that liquid.

label: sputum collection
definition: The process of collecting a portion of urine from an organism.

label: swabbing for specimen collection
definition: The process of collecting specimen material using a swab collection device.

label: vacuuming for specimen collection
definition: The removal or collection of specimen material through the use of suction.

label: necropsy
definition: A postmortem examination of the body of an animal to determine the cause of death or the character and extent of changes produced by disease.

label: environmental material collection process
definition: environmental_material_collection is an acquisition where an object is taken from an environment and put into a storage container.

label: specimen extraction device
definition: The tool or device used to extract a specimen.
help: Collection Devices are not always known, however when specified, they should be selected from an ontology controlled vocabulary.

label: Container
definition: An object that can be used to hold things.

label: Bag
definition: A sac or pouch.

label: Bottle
definition: A vessel with a narrow neck designed to accept a specific closure.

label: Vial
definition: A small, often stoppered glass or plastic bottle for holding medicines and chemicals.

label: Cryovial
definition: A vial used to store specimens in a cryopreservative at very low temperatures.

label: Glass Vial
definition: A glass container designed for use with parenteral drug products.

label: Plastic Vial
definition: A plastic container designed for use with parenteral drug products.

label: Swab
definition: A tuft of material on the end of a stick for applying solutions and suspensions
ui_definition: A portion of an absorbent material attached to one end of a small stick for the purpose of applying or collecting material.

label: Tube
definition: A hollow cylinder, especially one for holding or conveying liquids; anything shaped like such a hollow cylinder, e.
ui_definition: A hollow cylinder, especially one for holding or conveying liquids.

label: Vacutainer
definition: A brand of of test tube specifically designed for venipuncture; the tube contains a vacuum allowing it to suck blood though a needle and fill itself.

label: environmental material
definition: A portion of environmental material is a fiat object which forms the medium or part of the medium of an environmental system.
help: Food is considered to be a separate field from Environmental Material.

label: animal litter
definition: Straw or other material strewn in an animal's enclosure (e.

label: pig manure
definition: Manure which is primarily composed of pig feces.

label: anthropogenic environmental material
definition: Anthropogenic material in or on which organisms may live.

label: compost
definition: The aerobically decomposed remnants of organic materials.

label: gravel
definition: Gravel is an environmental material which is composed of pieces of rock that are at least two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension and no more than 75 millimeters.

label: mud
definition: A liquid or semi-liquid mixture of water and some combination of soil, silt, and clay.

label: organic material
definition: Environmental material derived from living organisms.

label: bodily fluid
definition: A natural bodily fluid or secretion such as blood, semen, saliva, blood plasma, intracellular and interstitial fluids.

label: excreta
definition: Excreta are bodily fluids consisting of waste matter, such as sweat or feces, discharged from the body.

label: feces
definition: Feces is an excreta consisting of waste products expelled from an animal's digestive tract through the anus (or cloaca) during defecation.

label: sand
definition: A naturally occurring granular material composed of finely divided rock and mineral particles.

label: sediment
definition: Sediment is an environmental substance comprised of any particulate matter that can be transported by fluid flow and which eventually is deposited as a layer of solid particles on the bedor bottom of a body of water or other liquid.

label: lake sediment
definition: Lake sediment is sediment which covers the bottom of a lake.

label: marine sediment
definition: Sediment which has been transported through the marine water column, settling on the seafloor.

label: deep marine sediment
definition: Sediment that accumulates in the flat or very gently sloping areas of the deep ocean basin floor.

label: soil
definition: Soil is an environmental material which is primarily composed of minerals, varying proportions of sand, silt, and clay, organic material such as humus, gases, liquids, and a broad range of resident micro- and macroorganisms.

label: loam
definition: A soil composed of sand, silt, and clay in relatively even concentration (about 40-40-20% concentration respectively).

label: waste material
definition: A material which is not the desired output of a process and which is typically the input of a process which removes it from its producer (e.

label: excreta
definition: Excreta are bodily fluids consisting of waste matter, such as sweat or feces, discharged from the body.

label: feces
definition: Feces is an excreta consisting of waste products expelled from an animal's digestive tract through the anus (or cloaca) during defecation.

label: waste water
definition: Water that has been adversely affected in quality by anthropogenic influence.

label: sewage
definition: Wastewater that is contaminated with feces or urine,

label: industrial wastewater
definition: Wastewater which is produced by industrial activity and which contains chemical contaminants other than those associated with urine and fecal matter.

label: gaseous environmental material
definition: A material entity which is composed of one or more chemical entities and has neither independent shape nor volume but tends to expand indefinitely.

label: air
definition: The mixture of gases (roughly (by molar content/volume: 78% nitrogen, 20.

label: ice
definition: An ice is an environmental material which is either frozen or which is maintained in a solid state by gravitational forces or pressure.

label: solid environmental material
definition: An environmental material which is in a solid state.

label: dust
definition: Minute solid particles with diameters less than 500 micrometers.

label: rock
definition: A rock is a naturally occurring solid aggregate of one or more minerals or mineraloids.

label: magma
definition: Magma is a mixture of molten or semi-molten rock, volatiles, and solids that is found beneath the uppermost solid layer of a planetary body.

label: liquid environmental material
definition: An environmental material which is in a liquid state.

label: water
definition: An environmental material primarily composed of dihydrogen oxide in its liquid form.

label: waste water
definition: Water that has been adversely affected in quality by anthropogenic influence.

label: sewage
definition: Wastewater that is contaminated with feces or urine,

label: industrial wastewater
definition: Wastewater which is produced by industrial activity and which contains chemical contaminants other than those associated with urine and fecal matter.

label: fresh water
definition: Water which has a low concentration of dissolved solutes, particularly that of sodium chloride.

label: drinking water
definition: Drinking water is water which may be consumed by humans with no adverse effects on their health.

label: driking water (purified)
definition: Drinking water that has been treated by heat, filtration, chemical disinfection, and/or exposure to ultraviolet radiation (including solar UV).

label: mineral water (as food source)
definition: Potable water that has a high content of dissolved minerals and may contain natural carbon dioxide.

label: environmental feature
definition: A material entity which determines an environmental system.
help: Food-related environmental locations may include, but are not exclusive to, food production, processing, distribution and retail environments that were sampled. Where Environmental Locations apply, descriptors should be selected from an ontology controlled vocabulary. Format: Ontology\nSource: GenEpiO slim, FoodOn slim, or EnvO

label: environmental zone
definition: An environmental zone is an environmental feature whose extent is determined by the presence or influence of one or more material entities or processes.

label: field
definition: An unbroken expanse (as of ice)

label: agricultural field
definition: An area of land, usually relatively small, enclosed or otherwise and used for agricultural purposes.

label: maize field
definition: A field  used for the cultivation of corn or related crop plants.

label: paddy field
definition: A flooded parcel of arable land used for growing rice and other semiaquatic crops.

label: clearing
definition: A tract of land with few or no trees in the middle of a wooded area.

label: mountain range
definition: A series of connected and aligned mountains or mountain ridges.

label: populated place
definition: Place or area with clustered or scattered buildings and a permanent human population.

label: dense settlement
definition: A settlement with a high density of buildings and inhabitants.

label: city
definition: Incorporated populated place.

label: township
definition: A township is a rural or sub-urban settlement.

label: vegetated area
definition: A vegetated area is a geographic feature which has ground cover dominated by plant communities.

label: grassland
definition: An area in which grasses (Graminae) are a significant component of the vegetation.

label: pasture
definition: Grassland used for grazing of ungulate livestock as part of a farm or ranch.

label: scrubland
definition: Area covered with low-growing or stunted perennial vegetation and usually not mixed with trees.

label: tundra
definition: Treeless, level, or gently rolling plains characteristic of arctic or subarctic regions, having a permanently frozen subsoil, and usually supporting low growing vegetation such as lichens, mosses, and stunted shrubs.

label: wetland
definition: An area that is inundated or saturated by surface or ground water at a frequency and duration sufficient to support, and that under normal circumstances do support, a prevalence of vegetation typically adapted for life in saturated soil conditions.

label: woodland
definition: Land having a cover of trees, shrubs, or both.

label: forest
definition: An area with a high density of trees.

label: mesoscopic physical object
definition: An environmental feature that is, or can be, contained and is predominantly composed of one or a few types of stuff.

label: manufactured product
definition: A material entity that has been processed by humans or their technology in any way, including intermediate products as well as final products.

label: hot tub
definition: A manufactured product which may hold a volume of heated water suitable for one or more humans to bathe in, usually for the purposes of hydrotherapy or pleasure.

label: manufactured cage
definition: A manufactured structure made of interspaced structural elements such as metal or wooden bars or wires held together such that they may be used to confine, contain, or protect something.

label: animal cage
definition: A manufactured cage which may be used to confine, contain, or protect an animal.

label: plumbing fixture
definition: An exchangeable device which can be connected to a plumbing system to deliver and drain water.

label: bathtub fixture
definition: A plumbing fixture which may serve as a container for water in which humans or other animals may bathe.

label: shower fixture
definition: A plumbing fixture within which a human or other animal may bathe under a spray of water.

label: sink fixture
definition: A plumbing fixture which is bowl-shaped and used for washing hands, dishwashing, and other purposes.

label: vehicle
definition: A vehicle is a mobile machine which transports people or cargo.

label: motor vehicle
definition: A motor vehicle is a vehicle which is propelled by an engine or motor and that does not operate on rails.

label: truck
definition: A truck is a motor vehicle which, as its primary funcion, transports cargo rather than human passangers.

label: food truck
definition: A truck which is equipped to cook and sell food.

label: animal feed
definition: Animal feed is a biotic mesoscopic physical object consisting of any foodstuff that is used specifically to feed domesticated livestock, such as cattle, goats, sheep, horses, chickens and pigs.

label: contaminated animal feed
definition: Contaminated animal feed is an animal feed that has become contaminated with or come contact with microorganisms or toxic chemicals.

label: plant feed
definition: Plant feed is a biotic mesoscopic physical object consisting of any foodstuff that is used specifically to feed plants.

label: bone meal
definition: A mixture of crushed and coarsely ground bones that is used as an organic fertilizer for plants and formerly in animal feed.

label: astronomical body part
definition: A material part of an astronomical body.

label: hydrographic feature
definition: A geographical feature associated with water.

label: layer
definition: A layer is a quantity of some material which has comparable thickness and usually covers some surface.

label: surface layer
definition: A surface layer is the uppermost layer of some material entity.

label: building floor
definition: A building floor is a surface layer which is part of a building and used for walking.

label: badland
definition: An arid terrain with clay-rich soil that has been extensively eroded by wind and water.

label: beach
definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a body of water.

label: cave
definition: Naturally formed, subterranean open area or chamber.

label: depression
definition: A landform sunken or depressed below the surrounding area.

label: channel of a watercourse
definition: The physical confine of a river, slough or ocean strait consisting of a bed and banks.

label: canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used for navigation, drainage or irrigation.

label: drainage canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used drainage.

label: ditch
definition: A small, human-made channel which has been dug for draining or irrigating the land.

label: drainage ditch
definition: A ditch that collects water from the surrounding land.

label: irrigation ditch
definition: A ditch that supplies water to surrounding land.

label: plumbing drain
definition: An artificial channel which transports unwanted water or waste liquids away from their source, either to a more useful area, a receptacle, or into sewers or stormwater mains as waste discharge to be released or processed.

label: desert
definition: A region rendered barren or partially barren by environmental extremes, especially by low rainfall.

label: plain
definition: A region of general uniform slope, comparatively level, and of considerable extent.

label: slope
definition: The part of an elevation or depression between the relatively flat surrounding area and the peak of a mount or the bottom of a depression.

label: terrace
definition: A step-like feature between higher and lower ground: a relatively flat or gently inclined shelf of earth, backed and fronted by steep slopes or manmade detaining walls.

label: tunnel
definition: An underground or underwater passage.

label: watershed
definition: The separation between neighbouring drainage basins (catchments).

label: channel
definition: A structure which traverses a mass of one or more environmental materials, and encloses a roughly tubular site.

label: tunnel
definition: An underground or underwater passage.

label: water body
definition: An accumulation of water of varying size.

label: lentic water body
definition: A lentic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, has very little to no directed flow.

label: lake
definition: A body of water or other liquid of considerable size contained on a body of land.

label: marine water body
definition: A significant accumulation of water which is part of a marine biome.

label: ocean
definition: Continuous saline-water bodies that surround the continents and fill the Earth's great depressions.

label: sea
definition: A large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean.

label: pond
definition: A body of water, usually of smaller size than a lake.

label: lotic water body
definition: A lotic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, is flowing.

label: spring
definition: A point where groundwater or steam flows out of the ground, and is thus where the aquifer surface meets the ground surface or where there is a fissure.

label: watercourse
definition: A flowing body of water.

label: canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used for navigation, drainage or irrigation.

label: drainage canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used drainage.

label: stream
definition: Linear body of water flowing on the Earth's surface.

label: river
definition: A stream which, through permanent or seasonal flow processes, moves from elevated land towards lower elevations through a definite channel and empties either into a sea, lake, or another river or ends on land as bed seepage and evapotranspiration exceed water supply.

label: anthropogenic geographic feature
definition: An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.

label: farm
definition: A tract of crop or grazing land, as well as the group of buildings with and often surrounding a farmhouse, including barns, sheds, and other outbuildings, used for agricultural production.

label: fish farm
definition: A facility in which fish are raised commercially in tanks or enclosures, usually for food.

label: fish hatchery
definition: A facility where eggs of fish are hatched under artificial conditions.

label: plantation
definition: An intentional planting of a crop, on a large scale, usually for uses other than cereal production or pasture.

label: feedlot
definition: A feedlot is a plot of land on which livestock are fattened for market

label: drylot
definition: A drylot is an enclosure of limited size usually bare of vegetation and used for fattening livestock.

label: construction
definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

label: building
definition: A permanent walled and roofed construction.

label: hospital
definition: A hospital is a building in which health care services are  provided by specialized staff and equipment.

label: house
definition: A house is a building that provides a dwelling-place for a living entity.

label: animal house
definition: A house used for sheltering non-human animals.

label: closed animal house
definition: An animal house which has a complete building envelope.

label: open animal house
definition: An animal house which is only partially surrounded by a building envelope.

label: residential building
definition: A human house which serves as a long-term shelter for its inhabitants and within which they store personal property.

label: industrial building
definition: An industrial building is a building within which goods are produced and, optionally, stored or within which services are rendered.

label: bakery
definition: A bakery is a building in which raw flour-based food is baked in an oven to produce food products such as bread, cakes, pastries, and pies.

label: brewery
definition: A brewery is a building in which alcoholic beverages are produced by brewing, that is, steeping a starch source (commonly cereal grains) in water and fermenting the resulting sweet liquid with yeast.

label: dairy
definition: A dairy is a building in which animal milk is harvested and, optionally, processed for human consumption.

label: food processing building
definition: A food processing building is a building in which materials that contain or consist of essential body nutrients - such as carbohydrates, fats, proteins, vitamins, or minerals - and may be ingested and assimilated by an organism to produce energy, stimulate growth, and maintain life are converted alternative forms.

label: fish processing building
definition: A building in which fish are subject to a series of operations to prepare them for human consumption.

label: abattoir
definition: A facility in which non-human animals are slaughtered and processed for human consumption.

label: shop
definition: A building in which a business presents a selection of goods and offers to trade or sell them to customers for money or other goods.

label: food shop
definition: A shop in which a business offers food products for sale or trade.

label: ethnic food shop
definition: A food shop in which the food products on offer are restricted to those produced in a region and cultural setting other than that of the shop's locality.

label: grocery store
definition: A food shop in which food products are the primary offer for sale or trade.

label: delicatessen
definition: A food shop which sells a selection of food products that are not typical dietary components of the human population it is co-located with.

label: grocery store
definition: A grocery store is a retail store that primarily sells food.

label: market
definition: A market, or marketplace, is a location where people regularly gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods

label: specialty/ethnic store
definition: A specialty/ethnic food store is a store specializing in a particular variety of food or food of cultural / regional origin.

label: day care building
definition: A building which is used to care for a human child during the working day by a person, outside the child's immediate family, other than that child's legal guardians.

label: food kiosk
definition: A kiosk from which food products are sold.

label: kiosk
definition: A booth with an open window on one side.

label: nursing home
definition: A building in which nursing aides and skilled nurses provide care and treatment to residents who have significant difficulty coping with the required activities of daily living.

label: restaurant
definition: A building within which food and drink are prepared and served to customers in exchange for money or other goods and/or services.

label: cafeteria
definition: A building which provides the site for food services with little or no waiting staff furnishing table service.

label: take-out restaurant
definition: A restaurant which provides prepared meals or other food products that the purchaser must eat off its premises.

label: building floor
definition: A building floor is a surface layer which is part of a building and used for walking.

label: constructed barrier
definition: A constructed barrier is a freestanding wall, berm, or fence built to limit movement of entities across a boundary.

label: dam
definition: A barrier constructed across a watercourse to control the flow or raise the level of water.

label: drainage canal
definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used drainage.

label: mine
definition: An excavation in the Earth for the purpose of extracting earth materials.

label: pier
definition: A raised walkway over water, supported by piles or pillars.

label: research facility
definition: A facility, permanent or temporary, on land, in air, space or water, where scientific research or measurements can be undertaken.

label: sports facility
definition: A building or region where sports activities can be carried out.

label: constructed swimming pool
definition: A construction which is designed to hold water in which humans may swim or perform other leisure activities.

label: water intake
definition: A hydraulic-engineering installation which transports water - in specified amounts, of a specified quality, and in accordance with a water-consumption plan - from a source of supply into a conduit.

label: garden
definition: An enclosure for displaying selected plant or animal life.

label: zoological garden
definition: A facility in which animals are confined within enclosures and displayed to the public, and in which they may also be bred.

label: petting zoo
definition: A petting zoo is a zoological garden which contains domesticated non-human animals and some wild non-human animals that are docile enough for humans to touch and feed.

label: park
definition: A bounded area of land, or water, usually in its natural or semi-natural (landscaped) state and set aside for some purpose, usually to do with recreation or conservation.

label: well
definition: A cylindrical hole, pit, or tunnel drilled or dug down to a depth from which water, oil, or gas can be pumped or brought to the surface.

label: campground
definition: A part of an ecosystem which may be or has been used for one or more overnight stays by humans sheltering in tents, camper vans, caravans, or improvised shelters.

label: dedicated campground
definition: A campground which has been modified by humans to provide and maintain facilities for camping such as fire pits, road access, latrines, and garbage bins.

label: impromptu campground
definition: A campground which has no pre-existing facilities installed or maintained by humans, usually found outside of anthropised ecosystems.

label: fairground
definition: A part of an ecosystem which has been allocated to host a gathering of people for multiple entertainment or commercial activities.

label: agricultural fairground
definition: A fairground which is used to exhibit agricultural technology, livestock, and farm-related activity.

label: market
definition: A part of an ecosystem where people gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods.

label: subject organism (host) taxonomic species
definition: The species of the host organism from which a specimen (pathogen) organism was obtained. Use the full taxonomic name, eg, "Homo sapiens".

label: subject health status (GSCID-BRC)
definition: A description of whether a given subject organism appeared healthy, sick or deceased at the time of specimen extraction. If sick or deceased, additional details should be provided in project-specific fields.

label: Healthy
definition: Having no significant health-related issues.

label: Pathologic
definition: Caused by or altered by or manifesting disease or pathology.

label: Death
definition: The cessation of life.

label: Accidental Death
definition: An indication that the subject's death was due to a mishap.

label: Brain Death
definition: Irreversible absence of cortical and brain stem functioning.

label: Cardiac Death
definition: The cessation of life due to heart abnormalities or disease.

label: Non-Sudden Cardiac Death
definition: An expected natural death from a cardiac cause.

label: Sudden Cardiac Death
definition: An unexpected natural death from a cardiac cause within a short time period from the onset of symptoms.

label: Death During, or within 90 Days of, Index Hospital Admission
definition: An indication that death occurred on or within 90 days of a patient's initial admission to a hospital.

label: Death Related to Adverse Event
definition: The termination of life associated with an adverse event.

label: Induction Death
definition: Death of the patient due to the toxic side effects of induction therapy.

label: Death by Natural Cause
definition: Death that is attributed to the progression of a disease or pre-existing condition, and which is not attributable to any outside action or force.

label: Died in a Medical Facility
definition: The patient died while in a medical center such as a hospital, skilled nursing facility (SNF), intermediate care facility (ICF), or a freestanding hospice center.

label: Early Intrauterine Death
definition: A death of the embryo occurring inside the uterus.

label: Intrauterine Fetal Death
definition: Death of a fetus after 10 weeks gestation.

label: Early Fetal Death
definition: Death of a fetus at 10 weeks, 0 days to 15 weeks, 6 days of gestation.

label: Late Fetal Death
definition: Death of a fetus at 16 weeks, 0 days to 19 weeks, 6 days of gestation.

label: Late Intrauterine Death
definition: A death of the fetus occurring inside the uterus.

label: Pediatric Death
definition: Death of a fetus, neonate, or patient 20 years or younger.

label: Neonatal Death
definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 28 days of life.

label: Early Neonatal Death
definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 7 days of life.

label: Late Neonatal Death
definition: Death of live newborn between 7and 27 days after birth.

label: Post-Natal Death at 16-20 Weeks Gestation
definition: A fetus of 16-20 weeks gestational age that shows signs of life at birth but dies after delivery.

label: Sudden Infant Death Syndrome
definition: Unexpected death in infancy which remains unexplained following autopsy, review of the medical history, and investigation of the death circumstances and death scene.

label: Very Early Neonatal Death
definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 24 hours of life

label: Perinatal Mortality
definition: Fetal or infant death during the period of time that includes the antepartum, intrapartum, and neonatal stages.

label: Post Neonatal Death
definition: Death between 28 days and 1 year of life.

label: Presumed Dead
definition: The status of an individual who in all likelihood is not living, but has not been officially declared dead.

label: Pronounced Dead
definition: The status of an individual is officially declared not living by an authority.

label: Stillbirth
definition: A fetus of at least 20 weeks gestation, or of a birth weight of at least 350 grams if the gestational age is unknown, that is born without signs of life at the time of delivery, and with an Apgar score of zero at both one and five minutes.

label: Antepartum Stillbirth
definition: Fetal death greater than or equal to 20 weeks of gestation prior to labor with Apgar scores of 0 at 1 minute, 5 minutes and beyond.

label: Early Stillbirth
definition: Delivery of a dead fetus greater than 22 weeks but less than 28 weeks gestational age, and/or whose birth weight is greater than 500 grams but less than 1,000 grams.

label: Intrapartum Stillbirth
definition: Fetal death greater than or equal to 20 weeks of gestation during labor with Apgar scores of 0 at 1 minute, 5 minutes and beyond.

label: Late Stillbirth
definition: Delivery of a dead fetus greater than 28 weeks gestational age and/or greater than 1,000 grams birth weight.

label: Sudden Death
definition: An unexpected death without warning.

label: Unscheduled Death
definition: The cessation of life at an unplanned time.

label: subject disease
definition: Name of disease in a subject that is related to a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

label: subject body product
definition: substance produced by the body, e.g. stool, mucus, where the specimen was obtained from.
help: Body Products may refer to animal or plant samples as well as clinical samples. Body Products are considered to be anatomical substances that can move through a body. Tissue types should be specified in the Anatomical Site field.

label: animal body product
definition: A product of an animal, as in blood, feces, sputum, etc.

label: bodily fluid
definition: Liquid components of living organisms.

label: blood serum
definition: The portion of blood plasma that excludes clotting factors.

label: haemolymphatic fluid
definition: Circulating fluid that is part of the hemolymphoid system.

label: blood
definition: A fluid that is composed of blood plasma and erythrocytes.

label: arterial blood
definition: A blood that is part of a artery.

label: capillary blood
definition: A blood that is part of a capillary.

label: umbilical cord blood
definition: blood that remains in the placenta and in the attached umbilical cord after childbirth[WP].

label: venous blood
definition: A blood that is part of a vein.

label: blood plasma
definition: The liquid component of blood, in which erythrocytes are suspended.

label: blood serum
definition: The portion of blood plasma that excludes clotting factors.

label: lymph
definition: Lymph is the fluid that is formed when interstitial fluid enters the conduits of the lymphatic system through lymph capillaries[WP].

label: saliva
definition: A fluid produced in the oral cavity by salivary glands, typically used in predigestion, but also in other functions.

label: secretion of serous gland
definition: Any fluid produced by a serous gland.

label: peritoneal fluid
definition: Transudate contained in the peritoneal cavity.

label: synovial fluid
definition: Joint fluid is a transudate of plasma that is actively secreted by synovial cells.

label: sputum
definition: Matter ejected from the lungs, bronchi, and trachea, through the mouth.

label: transudate
definition: Any bodily fluid that has passed through a membrane such as the capillary wall, as a result of unbalanced hydrostatic and osmotic forces

label: peritoneal fluid
definition: Transudate contained in the peritoneal cavity.

label: synovial fluid
definition: Joint fluid is a transudate of plasma that is actively secreted by synovial cells.

label: cerebrospinal fluid
definition: A clear, colorless, bodily fluid, that occupies the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain and spinal cord.

label: fluid - aspirate
definition: [WHICH DEFINITION?] See http://medical-dictionary.

label: egg yolk
definition: The yellow spheroidal mass of stored food that forms the inner portion of the egg of a bird or reptile and is surrounded by the white.

label: excreta
definition: A portion of organism substance that is the product of an excretion process that will be eliminated from the body.

label: excreted gas
definition: Any gaseous product of an excretory process.

label: gas excreted from digestive tract
definition: Any excreted gas that is produced by the digestive tract.

label: feces
definition: Portion of semisolid bodily waste discharged through the anus[MW,modified]

label: meconium
definition: A dark greenish mass that accumulates in the bowel during fetal life and is discharged shortly after birth.

label: urine
definition: Excretion that is the output of a kidney

label: down feather
definition: A feather lacking a vane and having a rudimentary rachis and a tuft of non-interlocked barbs with elongated barbules extending from the calamus

label: compost
definition: A mixture that consists largely of decayed organic matter and is used for fertilizing and conditioning land.

label: plant
definition: Any of a kingdom (Plantae) of living things typically lacking locomotive movement or obvious nervous or sensory organs and possessing cellulose cell walls.

label: plant rinse
definition: The process of rinsing plants with liquid with the objective of extracting specimens from that liquid.

label: subject anatomical site
definition: Name of body site where the specimen was obtained from, such as a specific organ or tissue.
help: Anatomical sites can pertain to both clinical, animal and plant samples. Materials that move through a body (e.g. feces, urine, blood) should be specified in the Body Products field.

label: anatomical structure
definition: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

label: acellular anatomical structure
definition: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

label: eggshell
definition: A product of the somatic follicle cell epithelium and a structure that supports the egg in a hostile environment, minimizing water loss whilst allowing gas exchanges essential for embryonic respiration[GO].

label: anatomical system
definition: Multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function.

label: respiratory system
definition: Functional system which consists of structures involved in respiration.

label: ectoderm-derived structure
definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the ectoderm.

label: ecto-epithelium
definition: Epithelium composed of cells that develops from the ectoderm[FMA,modified].

label: oral epithelium from ectoderm
definition: An epithelium that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a oral epithelium.

label: Rathkes pouch epithelium
definition: A epithelial sac that is part of a Rathke's pouch.

label: outer epithelium
definition: The epidermis is the entire outer epithelial layer of an animal, it may be a single layer that produces an extracellular material (e.

label: skin epidermis
definition: The outer epithelial layer of the skin that is superficial to the dermis.

label: ectodermal part of digestive tract
definition: A portion of the gut that is derived from ectoderm.

label: Rathkes pouch epithelium
definition: A epithelial sac that is part of a Rathke's pouch.

label: feather
definition: one of the epidermal growths that form the distinctive outer covering, or plumage, on birds.

label: down feather
definition: A feather lacking a vane and having a rudimentary rachis and a tuft of non-interlocked barbs with elongated barbules extending from the calamus

label: endoderm-derived structure
definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the endoderm.

label: bronchial lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of a bronchus.

label: endo-epithelium
definition: Epithelium that derives from the endoderm.

label: epithelium of foregut-midgut junction
definition: An epithelium that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

label: hepatic diverticulum
definition: An out-pocket of thickened ventral foregut epithelium adjacent to the developing heart.

label: endodermal part of digestive tract
definition: A portions of the gut that is derived from endoderm.

label: hepatic diverticulum
definition: An out-pocket of thickened ventral foregut epithelium adjacent to the developing heart.

label: gall bladder
definition: An organ that aids digestion and stores bile produced by the liver[WP].

label: liver
definition: An exocrine gland which secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat, synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood, synthesizes vitamin A, detoxifies poisonous substances, stores glycogen, and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes[GO].

label: lung
definition: Respiration organ that develops as an oupocketing of the esophagus.

label: right lung
definition: Lung which consists of the right upper lobe, middle lobe and right lower lobe.

label: oropharynx
definition: the portion of the pharynx that lies between the soft palate and the upper edge of the epiglottis

label: proximo-distal subdivision of respiratory tract
definition: An section of a respiratory tract.

label: nasopharynx
definition: the section of the pharynx that lies above the soft palate

label: respiratory tract
definition: Anatomical structure that is part of the respiratory system.

label: respiratory tube
definition: A tube in the respiratory system.

label: bronchus
definition: the upper conducting airways of the lung; these airways arise from the terminus of the trachea

label: trachea
definition: The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches [GO:dph].

label: tracheobronchial lymph node
definition: A lymph node located near the bifurcation of the trachea.

label: lateral structure
definition: Any structure that is placed on one side of the left-right axis of a bilaterian.

label: kidney
definition: A paired organ of the urinary tract which has the production of urine as its primary function.

label: left kidney
definition: A kidney that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: right kidney
definition: A kidney that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

label: lung
definition: Respiration organ that develops as an oupocketing of the esophagus.

label: right lung
definition: Lung which consists of the right upper lobe, middle lobe and right lower lobe.

label: mesoderm-derived structure
definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the mesoderm.

label: bone marrow
definition: the soft tissue that fills the cavities of bones

label: cloaca
definition: Common chamber into which the intestines and excretory system opens.

label: heart
definition: A myogenic muscular circulatory organ found in the vertebrate cardiovascular system composed of chambers of cardiac muscle.

label: hemopoietic organ
definition: Organ that is part of the hematopoietic system.

label: spleen
definition: the organ that functions to filter blood and to store red corpuscles and platelets

label: mesenteric lymph node
definition: The lymph nodes located in the mesentery, of which there are 3 classes: ileocolic, juxtaintestinal mesenteric, and central superior group.

label: muscle tissue
definition: Muscle tissue is a contractile tissue made up of actin and myosin fibers[GO].

label: subcutaneous lymph node
definition: A lymph node that is part of a hypodermis.

label: urethra
definition: the fibromuscular tubular canal through which urine is discharged from the bladder to the exterior via the external urinary meatus; in males, the urethra is joined by the ejaculatory ducts and serves as a passageway for semen during ejaculation, as well as a canal for urine during voiding; in females, the urethra is shorter and emerges above the vaginal opening

label: urinary bladder
definition: distensible musculomembranous organ situated in the anterior part of the pelvic cavity in which urine collects before excretion[MP].

label: morphological feature
definition: A part of an organism or organ that is continuous with its surroundings and distinguished from its surroundings based on morphology.

label: anatomical projection
definition: A projection or outgrowth of tissue from a larger body or organ.

label: integumentary projection
definition: Anatomical projection that is part of the integumentl system.

label: cutaneous appendage
definition: Anatomical projection that protrudes from the skin.

label: feather
definition: one of the epidermal growths that form the distinctive outer covering, or plumage, on birds.

label: down feather

label: sauteing

label: stir-frying

label: deep-frying

label: cooking with inherent fat or oil

label: food preservation process
definition: The methods contributing to the prevention or retardation of microbial, enzymatic or oxidative spoilage and thus to the extension of shelf life. Index all methods for which information is available, even if a corresponding descriptor has already been used in *H. TREATMENT APPLIED*. Preservation descriptors refer to the finished food as a whole with these exceptions: (1) if the components of a multi-component food, such as cream pie, are preservation by different methods, index all methods; (2)  if chemical preservatives are declared on the label, always index them even if it is known that the preservative was introduced through or is only present in a component or ingredient of the food; and (3) if the preservation method for an ingredient is declared on the label (such as brie cheese made from pasteurized milk) index it. Also use *INGREDIENT preservation by THERMAL PROCESSING* or *INGREDIENT preservation by IRRADIATION* when ingredients have been pasteurized, ultrapasteurized, sterilized or irradiated.

definition: preservation by use of chemical to destroy, suppress or inhibit undesirable microorganisms or enzyme activity.

definition: preservation by adding inorganic acids or salts (e.

label: preservation by brining
definition: Immersed in a salt brine strong enough to suppress enzyme activity and growth of undesirable organisms.

label: preservation by dry salting
definition: Packed in dry salt in sufficient quantity to suppress enzyme activity or growth of undesirable organisms.

label: preservation by chilling
definition: preservation by cooling and keeping at a temperature between 30°F and 45°F (-1°C and 7°C).

label: preservation by storage in refrigerating agent
definition: preservation by storage in refrigerating agent, e.

label: preservation by chilling or freezing
definition: preservation by cooling and storage at low temperature (chilling at around 0-5°C (32 to 41°F), freezing at -18°C (0°F))  to prevent or retard microbial or enzymatic spoilage.

label: preservation by fermentation
definition: preservation by suppressing undesirable microorganisms and enzymatic activity by the effects of fermentation.

label: preservation by filtration
definition: preservation by filtering out yeasts and molds, generally followed by aseptic packaging.

label: preservation by micro-filtration
definition: Microfiltration is used to remove undesirable micro-organisms and molecules.

label: preservation by ultra-filtration
definition: Separation of colloidal or very fine solid materials by filtration through microporous or semipermeable mediums.

label: preservation by freezing
definition: preservation by freezing a food product and keeping it at a temperature below the freezing point (20-30 degrees F) without regard to the product's physical state.

label: preservation by cryogenic freezing
definition: Frozen very rapidly by means of refrigerating agents such as liquid nitrogen or carbon dioxide.

label: preservation by heat treatment
definition: preservation by the use of high temperature for a time sufficient to reduce or destroy undesirable microorganisms and enzyme activity.

label: high temperature short time (htst) pasteurization
definition: High Temperature Short Time (HTST) pasteurization is one of the most common methods of pasteurization , which uses metal plates and hot water to raise milk temperatures to at least 72° C (161° F) for not less than 15 seconds, followed by rapid cooling.

label: higher heat shorter time (hhst) pasteurization
definition: Higher Heat Shorter Time (HHST) is a process similar to HTST pasteurization, but it uses slightly different equipment and higher temperatures (83 - 127° C) for a shorter time.

label: low-temperature-long-time (ltlt) pasteurization
definition: Low-Temperature-Long-Time Treatment (LTLT) uses low heat for a longer time to kill pathogenic bacteria.

label: ultra high temperature (uht) pasteurization
definition: Typically involves heating milk or cream to 135° to 150° C (275° to 302° F) for 1 or 2 seconds.

label: ultra pasteurization (up) by heat
definition: When used to describe a dairy product, means that such product shall have been thermally processed at or above 138° C (280° C) for at least 2 seconds, either before or after packaging so as to produce a product that has extended shelf life under refrigerated conditions (21 CFR 131.

label: preservation by blanching
definition: Short time scalding to stop emzymatic activity as vegetables being prepared for freezing.

label: preservation by sous vide
definition: Sous-vide (pronounced /su 'vid/), French for "under vacuum", is a method of cooking that is intended to maintain the integrity of ingredients by heating them for an extended period of time in vacuum sealed plastic pouches at relatively low temperatures.

label: sterilization by hot filling and cooling

preservation by irradiation
definition: preservation by the use of radiation to destroy or suppress undesirable microorganisms or enzyme activity.

label: preservation by electron accelerator radiation
definition: Treated by electron accelerator radiation, for example to kill insects in cereals.

label: preservation by ionizing radiation
definition: preservation by irradiation, primarily by gamma radiation.

preservation by reducing water activity
definition: Preservation method that lowers the water activity (relative humidity) of a food product.

label: preservation by adding sugar
definition: preservation by adding sugar, sugar syrup or by partial inversion of disaccharides until the sugar concentration is high enough to prevent growth of microorganisms.

label: osmotic dehydration
definition: Reduction of water in the product by osmosis.

label: peservation by heat drying
definition: Drying by heat.

label: artificial heat drying
definition: Drying by the application of artificial heat.

label: freeze-drying
definition: Dehydration by sublimation under reduced pressure while frozen.

label: natural heat drying
definition: Dried by natural heat, usually through exposure to the sun.

label: sun drying
definition: Drying by exposure to the sun.

label: preservation by brining
definition: Immersed in a salt brine strong enough to suppress enzyme activity and growth of undesirable organisms.

label: preservation by dry salting
definition: Packed in dry salt in sufficient quantity to suppress enzyme activity or growth of undesirable organisms.

label: preservation by smoking
definition: In the past, smoking was a useful preservation tool, in combination with other techniques, most commonly salt-curing or drying.

label: preservation by storage in modified atmosphere
definition: preservation by storage in an atmosphere in which the concentrations of oxygen and carbon dioxide are different from those in air.

label: preservation by storage in controlled atmosphere
definition: Storage of fruits and vegetables in an atmosphere in which the concentrations of oxygen, carbon dioxide (and often nitrogen) are different from those in air and at a low temperature.

label: preservation by storage in inert atmosphere
definition: preservation by storage in inert gases (e.

definition: Storing under reduced pressure (e.

label: sterilization by ultra high pressure
definition: Sterilized by holding at a high pressure, normally greater than 1000 bar.

label: food container or wrapping
definition: Type of container or wrapping defined by the main container material, the container form, and the material of the liner lids or ends. Also type of container or wrapping by form; prefer description by material first, then by form.  [FDA CFSAN 1995]
