definition: The medium in which the food is packed for preservation and handling or the medium surrounding homemade foods, e.g., peaches cooked in sugar syrup. The packing medium may provide a controlled environment for the food. It may also serve to improve palatability and consumer appeal.

label: packed in edible medium
definition: Packed in a medium that is also a food product.

label: packed in broth
definition: Packed in broth; includes meat, poultry or seafood packed in its' own juice.

label: draft sequence repository data - antibiogram
definition: A dataset of the minimal inhibitory concentrations (value, unit, sign (<,>, =)) and resistance phenotypes (resistant, sensitive or undetermined) of the sequenced isolate against different antibiotics tested.

label: Microbial Susceptibility Test
definition: A method to determine whether microbial growth is affected by an antimicrobial compound.

label: Agar Dilution Method
definition: A method to determine microbial susceptibility to antibiotics in which test bacteria is inoculated onto agar plates with serial dilutions of know quantities of antibiotics.

label: Disk Diffusion Method
definition: A method to determine microbial susceptibility to antibiotics in which filter paper disks containing known concentrations of antibiotics are placed on the agar surface that has been previously inoculated with the bacteria of interest.

label: Micro Broth Dilution Method
definition: A method to determine the minimum inhibitory concentration (MIC) of antibiotics in which growth media is pipetted into a multi-well plate.

label: Epsilometry
definition: A method to determine microbial susceptibility to antibiotics in which a plastic strip impregnated with the antibiotic of interest is placed on an agar plate that has been inoculated with bacteria.

label: antimicrobial resistance tissue specificity
definition: The tissue type used to select breakpoints from a particular standard, for the interpretation of MIC results.
help: Tissue Specificity (AST Breakpoint) only needs to be specified when the standard used to interpret the MIC requires this information e.g. selecting CLSI veterinary breakpoints.

label: female reproductive organ
definition: A female organ involved in reproduction

label: male reproductive organ
definition: A male organ involved in reproduction

label: skin epidermis
definition: The outer epithelial layer of the skin that is superficial to the dermis.

label: skin disease
definition: An integumentary system disease that is located_in skin.

label: skin lesion
definition: Skin lesion is a skin and integumentary tissue symptom characterized as an abnormal change in structure of the skin that is especially circumscribed and well defined due to injury or disease.

label: abscess
definition: A circumscribed collection of purulent exudate frequently associated with swelling and other signs of inflammation.

label: Cutaneous abscess
definition: A circumscribed area of pus or necrotic debris in the skin.

label: respiratory system disease
definition: A disease of anatomical entity that located_in the respiratory system which extends from the nasal sinuses to the diaphragm.

label: lower respiratory tract disease
definition: A respiratory system disease which involves the lower respiratory tract.

label: lung disease
definition: A lower respiratory tract disease in which the function of the lungs is adversely affected by narrowing or blockage of the airways resulting in poor air flow, a loss of elasticity in the lungs that produces a decrease in the total volume of air that the lungs are able to hold, and clotting, scarring, or inflammation of the blood vessels that affect the ability of the lungs to take up oxygen and to release carbon dioxide.

label: respiratory failure
definition: A lung disease characterized by inadequate gas exchange by the respiratory system.

label: adult respiratory distress syndrome
definition: A respiratory failure that results from diffuse injury to the endothelium of the lung (as in sepsis, chest trauma, massive blood transfusion, aspiration of the gastric contents, or pneumonia) and is characterized by pulmonary edema with an abnormally high amount of protein in the edematous fluid and by difficult rapid breathing and hypoxemia.

label: newborn respiratory distress syndrome
definition: A respiratory failure that is characterized by deficiency of the surfactant coating the inner surface of the lungs, by failure of the lungs to expand and contract properly during breathing with resulting collapse, and by the accumulation of a protein-containing film lining the alveoli and their ducts.

label: acute cystitis
definition: A cystitis characterized by a sudden onset or severe symptoms.

label: draft antibiogram drug test model
definition: This is the minimal set of parameters for drug test results for a particular antimicrobial agent.

label: antimicrobial resistance test drug
definition: This is a collection of drugs used to test antimicrobial resistance.
help: Standard chemical or generic drug names, rather than common or brand names, should be selected from an ontology controlled vocabulary.

label: acridine
definition: A polycyclic heteroarene that is anthracene in which one of the central CH groups is replaced by a nitrogen atom.

label: antibiotic antifungal agent
definition: Heteroorganic entities that are microbial metabolites (or compounds derived from them) which have significant antifungal properties.

label: antibiotic antifungal drug
definition: Any antibiotic antifungal agent used to treat fungal infections in humans or animals.

label: streptomycin
definition: A amino cyclitol glycoside that consists of streptidine having a disaccharyl moiety attached at the 4-position.

label: antibiotic fungicide
definition: Any antibiotic antifungal agent that has been used as a fungicide.

label: streptomycin
definition: A amino cyclitol glycoside that consists of streptidine having a disaccharyl moiety attached at the 4-position.

label: apramycin
definition: An aminoglycoside that is 2-deoxystreptamine that is substituted on the oxygen at position 4 by an (8R)-2-amino-8-O-(4-amino-4-deoxy-alpha-D-glucopyranosyl)-2,3,7-trideoxy-7-(methylamino)-D-glycero-alpha-D-allo-octodialdo-1,5:8,4-dipyranos-1-yl) group.

label: azole
definition: Any monocyclic heteroarene consisting of a five-membered ring containing nitrogen.

label: diazole
definition: An azole that is either one of a pair of heterocyclic organic compounds comprising three carbon atoms and two nitrogen atoms arranged in a ring.

label: imidazoles
definition: A five-membered organic heterocycle containing two nitrogen atoms at positions 1 and 3, or any of its derivatives; compounds containing an imidazole skeleton.

label: metronidazole
definition: A member of the class of imidazoles substituted at C-1, -2 and -5 with 2-hydroxyethyl, nitro and methyl groups respectively.

label: tinidazole
definition: 1H-imidazole substituted at C-1 by a (2-ethylsulfonyl)ethyl group, at C-2 by a methyl group and at C-5 by a nitro group.

label: oxazole
definition: An azole based on a five-membered heterocyclic aromatic skeleton containing one N and one O atom.

label: pristinamycin IIA
definition: A macrolide that is (together with pristinamycin IA) a component of pristinamycin, an oral streptogramin antibiotic produced by Streptomyces pristinaespiralis.

label: isoxazoles
definition: Oxazoles in which the N and O atoms are adjacent.

label: sulfamethoxazole
definition: An isoxazole (1,2-oxazole) compound having a methyl substituent at the 5-position and a 4-aminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 3-position.

label: sulfisoxazole
definition: A sulfonamide antibacterial with an oxazole substituent.

label: pyrroles
definition: An azole that includes only one N atom and no other heteroatom as a part of the aromatic skeleton.

label: coumermycin A1
definition: A hydroxycoumarin antibiotic that is obtained from Streptomyces rishiriensis and exhibits potent antibacterial and anticancer activity.

label: tetrazoles
definition: An azole in which the five-membered heterocyclic aromatic skeleton contains four N atoms and one C atom.

label: cefazolin
definition: A cephalosporin compound having [(5-methyl-1,3,4-thiadiazol-2-yl)sulfanyl]methyl and (1H-tetrazol-1-ylacetyl)amino side-groups.

label: thiazoles
definition: An azole in which the five-membered heterocyclic aromatic skeleton contains a N atom and one S atom.

label: cefotaxime
definition: A cephalosporin compound having acetoxymethyl and [2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetyl]amino side groups.

label: ceftaroline fosamil
definition: A cephalosporin that is the N-phospho prodrug of ceftaroline.

label: ceftriaxone
definition: A cephalosporin compound having 2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetylamino and [(2-methyl-5,6-dioxo-1,2,5,6-tetrahydro-1,2,4-triazin-3-yl)sulfanyl]methyl side-groups.

label: triazoles
definition: An azole in which the five-membered heterocyclic aromatic skeleton contains three N atoms and two C atoms.

label: tazobactam
definition: A member of the class of penicillanic acids that is sulbactam in which one of the exocyclic methyl hydrogens is replaced by a 1,2,3-triazol-1-yl group; used (in the form of its sodium salt) in combination with ceftolozane sulfate for treatment of complicated intra-abdominal infections and complicated urinary tract infections.

label: beta-lactam antibiotic
definition: An organonitrogen heterocyclic antibiotic that contains a beta-lactam ring.

label: carbacephem
definition: Any member of a group of synthetic antibiotics, similar to cephems but with carbon substituted for the sulfur; all possessing an acylated amine functionality at C-6 and (S,R) stereochemistry at C-6 and C-7.

label: loracarbef anion
definition: The conjugate base of loracarbef.

label: carbapenems
definition: The class of beta-lactam antibiotics that whose members have a carbapenem skeleton which is variously substituted at positions 3, 4, and 6.

label: ertapenem
definition: Meropenem in which the one of the two methyl groups attached to the amide nitrogen is replaced by hydrogen while the other is replaced by a 3-carboxyphenyl group.

label: meropenem
definition: A carbapenemcarboxylic acid in which the azetidine and pyrroline rings carry 1-hydroxymethyl and in which the azetidine and pyrroline rings carry 1-hydroxymethyl and 5-(dimethylcarbamoyl)pyrrolidin-3-ylthio substituents respectively.

label: imipenem
definition: A broad-spectrum, intravenous beta-lactam antibiotic of the carbapenem subgroup.

label: cephalosporin
definition: A class of beta-lactam antibiotics differing from the penicillins in having a 6-membered, rather than a 5-membered, side ring.

label: cefaclor
definition: A cephalosporin bearing chloro and (R)-2-amino-2-phenylacetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefadroxil
definition: A cephalosporin bearing methyl and  (2R)-2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefalotin
definition: A semisynthetic, first-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with acetoxymethyl and (2-thienylacetyl)nitrilo moieties at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the core structure.

label: cefamandole
definition: A cephalosporin compound having (R)-mandelamido and N-methylthiotetrazole side-groups.

label: cefazolin
definition: A cephalosporin compound having [(5-methyl-1,3,4-thiadiazol-2-yl)sulfanyl]methyl and (1H-tetrazol-1-ylacetyl)amino side-groups.

label: cefdinir
definition: A cephalosporin compound having 7beta-2-(2-amino-thiazol-4-yl)-2-[(Z)-hydroxyimino]-acetylamino- and 3-vinyl side groups.

label: cefditoren
definition: A broad spectrum, third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with (Z)-2-(4-methyl-1,3-thiazol-5-yl)ethenyl and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefepime
definition: A cephalosporin bearing (1-methylpyrrolidinium-1-yl)methyl and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefixime
definition: A third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic bearing vinyl and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-[(carboxymethoxy)imino]acetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefmetazole
definition: A cephalosporin antibiotic containg an N(1)-methyltetrazol-5-ylthiomethyl side-chain at C-3 of the parent cephem bicyclic structure.

label: cefonicid
definition: A cephalosporin bearing {[1-(sulfomethyl)-1H-tetrazol-5-yl]sulfanyl}methyl and (R)-2-hydroxy-2-phenylacetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefoperazone
definition: A semi-synthetic parenteral cephalosporin with a tetrazolyl moiety that confers beta-lactamase resistance.

label: cefotaxime
definition: A cephalosporin compound having acetoxymethyl and [2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetyl]amino side groups.

label: cefotiam
definition: A cephalosporin with ({1-[2-(dimethylamino)ethyl]-1H-tetrazol-5-yl}sulfanyl)methyl and (2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)acetamido substituents at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefoxitin
definition: A semisynthetic cephamycin antibiotic which, in addition to the methoxy group at the 7alpha position, has 2-thienylacetamido and carbamoyloxymethyl side-groups.

label: cefpodoxime
definition: A third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with methoxymethyl and (2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetamino substituents at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cefprozil
definition: A semisynthetic, second-generation cephalosporin, with prop-1-enyl and (R)-2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: ceftaroline fosamil
definition: A cephalosporin that is the N-phospho prodrug of ceftaroline.

label: ceftazidime
definition: A cephalosporin bearing pyridinium-1-ylmethyl and {[(2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-{[(2-carboxypropan-2-yl)oxy]imino}acetamido groups at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: ceftibuten
definition: A third-generation cephalosporin antibiotic with a [(2Z)-2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-4-carboxybut-2-enoyl]amino substituent at the 7 position of the cephem skeleton.

label: ceftizoxime
definition: A parenteral third-generation cephalosporin, bearing a 2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetyl]amino group at the 7beta-position.

label: ceftriaxone
definition: A cephalosporin compound having 2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetylamino and [(2-methyl-5,6-dioxo-1,2,5,6-tetrahydro-1,2,4-triazin-3-yl)sulfanyl]methyl side-groups.

label: cephalexin
definition: A semisynthetic first-generation cephalosporin antibiotic having methyl and beta-(2R)-2-amino-2-phenylacetamido groups at the 3- and 7- of the cephem skeleton, respectively.

label: cephapirin
definition: A cephalosporin with  acetoxymethyl and 2(pyridin-4-ylsulfanyl)acetamido substituents at positions 3 and 7, respectively, of the cephem skeleton.

label: cephradine
definition: A cephalosporin with a methyl substituent at position 3, and a (2R)-2-amino-2-cyclohexa-1,4-dien-1-ylacetamido substituent at position 7, of the cephem skeleton.

label: moxalactam
definition: A broad-spectrum oxacephem antibiotic in which the oxazine ring is substituted with a tetrazolylthiomethyl group and the azetidinone ring carries methoxy and 2-carboxy-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetamido substituents.

label: cephamycin
definition: Any member of the cephamycin sub-group of cephem antibiotics, differing from cephalosporins in possessing a methoxy group at the 7alpha-position of the cephem nucleus, and in being resistant to beta-lactamase.

label: cefoxitin
definition: A semisynthetic cephamycin antibiotic which, in addition to the methoxy group at the 7alpha position, has 2-thienylacetamido and carbamoyloxymethyl side-groups.

label: monobactam
definition: Monocyclic, bacterially produced or semisynthetic beta-lactam antibiotic.

label: aztreonam
definition: A synthetic monocyclic beta-lactam antibiotic (monobactam).

label: oxacephem
definition: Any member of the oxacephem sub-group of cephem antibiotics, in which the thiaazabicyclo moiety of the cephalosporins is replaced by an oxaazabicyclo moiety, and  where R3 is -H or -OCH3.

label: moxalactam
definition: A broad-spectrum oxacephem antibiotic in which the oxazine ring is substituted with a tetrazolylthiomethyl group and the azetidinone ring carries methoxy and 2-carboxy-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetamido substituents.

label: penams
definition: Natural and synthetic antibiotics containing the 4-thia-1-azabicyclo[3.

label: penam
definition: Compound comprising a beta-lactam ring fused to a saturated 5-membered ring containing one sulfur atom.

label: penicillin
definition: Any member of the group of substituted penams containing two methyl substituents at position 2, a carboxylate substituent at position 3 and a carboxamido group at position 6.

label: ampicillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-amino-2-phenylacetamido group.

label: azlocillin
definition: A semisynthetic penicillin antibiotic used in treating infections caused by Pseudomonas aeruginosa, Escherichia coli, and Haemophilus influenzae.

label: carbenicillin
definition: A penicillin antibiotic having a 6beta-2-carboxy-2-phenylacetamido side-chain.

label: cloxacillin
definition: A semisynthetic penicillin antibiotic carrying a 3-(2-chlorophenyl)-5-methylisoxazole-4-carboxamido group at position 6.

label: dicloxacillin
definition: A penicillin that is 6-aminopenicillanic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a 3-(2,6-dichlorophenyl)-5-methyl-1,2-oxazol-4-yl]formyl group.

label: flucloxacillin
definition: A penicillin compound having a 6beta-[3-(2-chloro-6-fluorophenyl)-5-methyl-1,2-oxazole-4-carboxamido] side-chain.

label: methicillin
definition: A penicillin that is 6-aminopenicillanic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a 2,6-dimethoxybenzoyl group.

label: mezlocillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a (2R)-2-[3-(methanesulfonyl)-2-oxoimidazolidine-1-carboxamido]-2-phenylacetamido group.

label: penicillin allergen
definition: Any penicillin which causes the onset of an allergic reaction.

label: amoxicillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetamido group.

label: benzylpenicillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a phenylacetamido group.

label: piperacillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-[(4-ethyl-2,3-dioxopiperazin-1-yl)carboxamido]-2-phenylacetamido group.

label: ticarcillin
definition: A penicillin compound having a 6beta-[(2R)-2-carboxy-2-thiophen-3-ylacetyl]amino side-group.

label: tazobactam
definition: A member of the class of penicillanic acids that is sulbactam in which one of the exocyclic methyl hydrogens is replaced by a 1,2,3-triazol-1-yl group; used (in the form of its sodium salt) in combination with ceftolozane sulfate for treatment of complicated intra-abdominal infections and complicated urinary tract infections.

label: bicozamycin
definition: A commercially important azabicyclic antibiotic obtained from Streptomyces sapporonensis.

definition: The class of beta-lactam antibiotics that whose members have a carbapenem skeleton which is variously substituted at positions 3, 4, and 6.

label: cefoxitin

label: ceftriaxone
definition: A cephalosporin compound having 2-(2-amino-1,3-thiazol-4-yl)-2-(methoxyimino)acetylamino and [(2-methyl-5,6-dioxo-1,2,5,6-tetrahydro-1,2,4-triazin-3-yl)sulfanyl]methyl side-groups.

definition: A penicillin that is 6-aminopenicillanic acid in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a 2,6-dimethoxybenzoyl group.

label: mezlocillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a (2R)-2-[3-(methanesulfonyl)-2-oxoimidazolidine-1-carboxamido]-2-phenylacetamido group.

label: penicillin allergen
definition: Any penicillin which causes the onset of an allergic reaction.

label: amoxicillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-amino-2-(4-hydroxyphenyl)acetamido group.

label: benzylpenicillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a phenylacetamido group.

label: piperacillin
definition: A penicillin in which the substituent at position 6 of the penam ring is a 2-[(4-ethyl-2,3-dioxopiperazin-1-yl)carboxamido]-2-phenylacetamido group.

label: ticarcillin
definition: A penicillin compound having a 6beta-[(2R)-2-carboxy-2-thiophen-3-ylacetyl]amino side-group.

label: rifampicin
definition: A member of the class of rifamycins that is a a semisynthetic antibiotic derived from Amycolatopsis rifamycinica (previously known as Amycolatopsis mediterranei and Streptomyces mediterranei)

label: fleroxacin
definition: A fluoroquinolone antibiotic that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline which is substituted at positions 1, 3, 6, 7 and 8 by 2-fluoroethyl, carboxy, fluoro, 4-methylpiperazin-1-yl and fluoro groups, respectively.

label: ofloxacin
definition: An oxazinoquinolone carrying carboxy, fluoro, methyl and 4-methylpiperazino substituents.

label: levofloxacin
definition: An optically active form of ofloxacin having (S)-configuration; an inhibitor of bacterial topoisomerase IV and DNA gyrase

label: pefloxacin
definition: A quinolone that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline which is substituted at positions 1, 3, 6 and 7 by ethyl, carboxy, fluorine, and 4-methylpiperazin-1-yl groups, respectively.

label: ciprofloxacin
definition: A  quinolone that is quinolin-4(1H)-one bearing cyclopropyl, carboxylic acid, fluoro and piperazin-1-yl substituents at positions 1, 3, 6 and 7, respectively.

label: enoxacin
definition: A 1,8-naphthyridine derivative that is 1,4-dihydro-1,8-naphthyridine with an ethyl group at the 1 position, a carboxy group at the 3-position, an oxo sustituent at the 4-position, a fluoro substituent at the 5-position and a piperazin-1-yl group at the 7 position.

label: gatifloxacin
definition: A monocarboxylic acid that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline-3-carboxylic acid which is substituted on the nitrogen by a cyclopropyl group and at positions 6, 7, and 8 by fluoro, 3-methylpiperazin-1-yl, and methoxy groups, respectively.

label: lomefloxacin
definition: A fluoroquinolone antibiotic, used (generally as the hydrochloride salt) to treat bacterial infections including bronchitis and urinary tract infections.

label: norfloxacin

definition: A macrolide that is (together with pristinamycin IA) a component of pristinamycin, an oral streptogramin antibiotic produced by Streptomyces pristinaespiralis.

label: puromycin
definition: An aminonucleoside antibiotic, derived from the Streptomyces alboniger bacterium, that causes premature chain termination during translation taking place in the ribosome.

label: pyrimidines

label: sulfadiazine
definition: A sulfonamide consisting of pyrimidine with a 4-aminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 2-position.

label: sulfadoxine
definition: A sulfonamide consisting of pyrimidine having methoxy substituents at the 5- and 6-positions and a 4-aminobenzenesulfonamido group at the 4-position.

label: sulfamethazine

label: clindamycin
definition: A carbohydrate-containing antibiotic that is the  semisynthetic derivative of lincomycin, a natural antibiotic.

label: ertapenem
definition: Meropenem in which the one of the two methyl groups attached to the amide nitrogen is replaced by hydrogen while the other is replaced by a 3-carboxyphenyl group.

label: lincomycin
definition: A carbohydrate-containing antibiotic produced by the actinomyces Streptomyces lincolnensis.

label: meropenem
definition: A carbapenemcarboxylic acid in which the azetidine and pyrroline rings carry 1-hydroxymethyl and in which the azetidine and pyrroline rings carry 1-hydroxymethyl and 5-(dimethylcarbamoyl)pyrrolidin-3-ylthio substituents respectively.

label: ciprofloxacin
definition: A  quinolone that is quinolin-4(1H)-one bearing cyclopropyl, carboxylic acid, fluoro and piperazin-1-yl substituents at positions 1, 3, 6 and 7, respectively.

label: bedaquiline

definition: A quinolone that is 4-oxo-1,4-dihydroquinoline which is substituted at positions 1, 3, 6 and 7 by ethyl, carboxy, fluorine, and 4-methylpiperazin-1-yl groups, respectively.

label: quinolone antibiotic
definition: An organonitrogen heterocyclic antibiotic whose structure contains a quinolone or quinolone-related skeleton.
